Adds a new KeePass entry.

Adds a new KeePass entry. The database must be opened first. The name of a top-level group/folder in KeePass and an entry title are mandatory, but all other arguments are optional. The password is passed in as SecureString or, if any, you can specify the EntryPasswordComplex end EntryPasswordLenght parameter to auto generate, the SecureString is converted to plaintext and then saved to the KeePass entry.
The previously-opened KeePass database object.

The MasterKey Password to open da KeePass Database. It is a PowerShell SecureString object , typically created with the New-KPSecurePassword cmdlet and recovered witch Get-KPSecurePassword cmdlet. If not is specified, the cmdlet get the KPSecurePassword stored with the label 'Default'. The same way that the command (Get-KPSecurePassword -Alias Default).MasterPassword. This parameter accept a objetc System.Security.SecureString as well.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: New-KPEntry -KeyPassFile D:\temp\Database.kdbx -GroupPath \MySQL\Dev -EntryTitle "MySql Dev" -EntryUserName myuser -EntryPasswordLenght 10 -EntryPasswordComplex -EntryUrl http://mysql.mycompany -EntryNotes "Important Notes" -Tags Tag1,Tag2,Tag3 -PassThru
